fields.indexing_notes: FEAST: Olei infirmorum. First statement of Hymn Chorus is interlined in later hand above the rubric, ymnus. The second statement of the chorus is in full form. "Audi judex" verse is notated in red ink.

und.value: O redemptor audi judex mortuorum una spes mortalium audi voces perferentum donum pacis pervivum o redemptor sume carmine temet concientium afflit nostris pater votis qui invisibiliter preconsortibus unxit te oleo letitie o redemptor afflit flamen sacrosanctam olim perdilivium quod ramus tulit olive ad arcam aecclesie o redemptor stans ad aram immo supplex infulatus pontifex debitum persolvit omne consecrato christmate o redemptor consecare tu dignare rex perennis patriae hoc olivum signum vivum contra lura daemonum o redemptor ut novetur sexus omnis unctione chrismatis et medetur sauciata dignitatis gloria o redemptor lota mente sacro fonte aufuguntur crimina uncta fronte sacrosancta influunt charismata o redemptor corde natus ex parentis aluum implens virginis praesta lucem claude noctem crismatis consortibus o redemptor sit haec dies festa nobis saeculorum saeculis sit sacrata digna laude nec senescat tempore o redemptor
